Subject: [ghostium] RTCPeerConnection ICE candidate filter hook

Spec-G wiring. Anchors at top of two Blink files. The real calls
into ``FingerprintNoiseSource::WebRTCPolicyOverride`` and
``WebRTCMdnsOnlyOverride`` land at:

  * ``RTCPeerConnection`` constructor in ``rtc_peer_connection.cc``,
    where ``WebRTCPolicyOverride`` clamps the
    ``RTCConfiguration.iceTransportPolicy`` and the deeper
    ``WebRTCIPHandlingPolicy`` enum so that a profile setting of
    ``kDefaultPublicInterfaceOnly`` / ``kDisableNonProxiedUdp`` /
    ``kDisableBoth`` overrides the page's request.
  * ``RTCIceCandidate`` materialisation in ``rtc_ice_candidate.cc``,
    where ``WebRTCMdnsOnlyOverride`` filters out host-type candidates
    whose addresses are raw IPs (keeping mdns ``.local`` candidates).

The two predicates compose: a profile that sets both ``policy`` and
``mdns_only`` applies both filters to every gathered candidate.

